(Beat drops, heavy bass, slow tempo)

**[Intro]**
Yo, check the mic, one two, one two.
We talkin' 'bout the big boss, the money crew.
Not the streets, not the block, but the bank down the hall.
The Federal Reserve, yeah, they runnin' the ball.
Listen up, homie, let me break it down low.

**[Verse 1]**
See, the Fed's like the DJ spinin' the tracks,
Decidin' how fast or how slow that the cash flow backs.
They got the "Interest Rate," that's the price of the loan,
If they crank it up high, you gotta pay more on your throne.
Borrowin' money gets expensive, like rent on the block,
So folks spend less, and the whole economy stops.
But if they drop the rate, yeah, they cuttin' the cost,
Suddenly everybody's buyin', nobody's lost.
They tryna keep the game balanced, no inflation spike,
So your dollar don't turn into a cheap plastic bike.
They watch the prices, keepin' 'em steady and cool,
Like a referee blowin' the whistle, breakin' the rule.

**[Chorus]**
It's the Fed, the Fed, keepin' the system tight,
Make sure the money flowin' smooth from the day to the night.
No crash, no boom, just a steady ride,
Keepin' the economy chill, keepin' the hype inside.
Yeah, the Federal Reserve, holdin' the keys,
Decidin' who gets the green and who gets the breeze.

**[Verse 2]**
Now, when the market gets shaky, like a floor full of cracks,
The Fed steps in quick, puttin' cash in the stacks.
They buy up the bonds, pumpin' liquidity in,
So the banks got the funds to let the people win.
It's like a bailout, a lifeline, a safety net,
Catchin' the whole city before it gets wet.
They print the paper, yeah, they control the supply,
Make sure there's enough cash so the people don't cry.
But if they print too much? Man, the prices go up,
Your dollar buys less, and the cup runneth up.
So they gotta be smart, gotta read the whole room,
Keepin' the inflation monster from comin' to doom.

**[Bridge]**
They ain't the President, they ain't the Mayor,
They work in the shadows, keepin' the ledger fair.
Independent crew, doin' what they gotta do,
So your paycheck don't vanish and turn into blue.
From the streets to the suits, from the hood to the bank,
They keep the whole system from takin' a tank.

**[Outro]**
So next time you hear 'bout the rate goin' up or down,
Remember the Fed is the king wearin' the crown.
Keepin' the game real, keepin' the money sound,
The Federal Reserve, yeah, they holdin' the ground.
Peace.
